| **Market Analysis** <br/> (Existing Solutions, Competition)                         | - Assess if mature solutions already exist.<br/>- Evaluate unique differentiators vs. competition.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | - **Competitive Advantage:** Building a unique, customized system could differentiate your offerings.<br/>- **High Risk:** If commercial solutions are strong, building might be duplicating existing capabilities.                                                                                                                                                                      | - **Proven Tools:** If established vendors have strong offerings, buying reduces risk and accelerates adoption.<br/>- **Limited Differentiation:** Off-the-shelf solutions might not set you apart if competitors use the same tools.                                                                                                                                                     | - **Uncertain Market:** If solutions are evolving or new players might enter, waiting may reveal better options or more favorable pricing.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| **Vendor Evaluation** <br/> (Reputation, SLAs)                                      | - Relevant if buying or forming tech partnerships.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            | - **Not Applicable to Building:** Except for potential third-party components or frameworks.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               | - **Critical Factor:** Must assess vendor’s stability, SLAs, track record, and alignment with your compliance needs.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | - **Watch Vendor Landscape:** New entrants or acquisitions might change the vendor market, offering better terms or features in the near future.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| **Future-Proofing** <br/> (Adapt to New Tech/Use Cases)                             | - Capability to incorporate new data sources, analysis techniques over time.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | - **Maximum Flexibility:** Own codebase can adapt to changing tech demands if well-architected.<br/>- **Requires Ongoing Investment:** Must continuously invest in R&D to stay current with emerging technologies.                                                                                                                                                                        | - **Vendor Updates:** Leverage vendor’s R&D for new features; you stay relatively hands-off on technical evolution.<br/>- **Less Direct Control:** Must rely on the vendor’s roadmap to adopt cutting-edge features.                                                                                                                                                                       | - **Rapidly Changing Tech:** If you expect a major leap in AI or data integration soon, waiting could avoid implementing a solution that quickly becomes outdated.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| **Risk Assessment** <br/> (Identification, Mitigation)                              | - Evaluate potential pitfalls (compliance, security, vendor lock-in, skill gaps).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | - **Own the Risk / Own the Reward:** You manage all project risks, but you also retain full control over how they are addressed.<br/>- **Custom Risk Management:** If you have strong governance, building can reduce reliance on external parties.                                                                                                                                          | - **Shared or Vendor-Assumed Risk:** Vendor covers some aspects (infrastructure security, performance SLAs), lowering your direct responsibility.<br/>- **Vendor Lock-In Risk:** Could face difficulties migrating to another solution if the contract changes or the vendor raises costs.                                                                                                   | - **Uncertain Future Landscape:** If the environment is volatile (regulations, technology, budgets), waiting reduces the risk of investing in the wrong solution.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    |
| **Decision Criteria**                                                              | **—**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        | **—**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | **—**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | **—**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              |
| **Build** <br/> (High Customization, In-House Expertise)                           | - **Control and Customization:** Full feature ownership, tailor everything to your workflows. <br/>- **Resources & Expertise:** Need skilled team & budget. <br/>- **Cost:** High upfront, potentially lower ongoing if usage is massive or indefinite. <br/>- **Time:** Flexible timeline, invests in strategic advantage. <br/>- **Strategic Fit:** Core to your unique value proposition or compliance needs.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     | **Applies fully to the “Build” path**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | **Contrasts with “Buy”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | **Contrasts with “Wait”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| **Buy** <br/> (Rapid Deployment, Lower Upfront, Mature Features)                   | - **Time to Market:** Quick solution with tested features. <br/>- **Cost:** Lower initial cost, predictable licensing/subscriptions. <br/>- **Functionality:** Usually meets standard requirements out-of-the-box. <br/>- **Risk:** Lower risk of project failure, but risk of vendor lock-in or limited customization. <br/>- **Resources:** Freed to focus on core business.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | **Contrasts with “Build”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              | **Applies fully to the “Buy” path**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            | **Contrasts with “Wait”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| **Wait** <br/> (Not Urgent, Anticipate Better Solutions)                           | - **Market Readiness:** Tools are rapidly evolving; waiting may yield more mature or cheaper solutions. <br/>- **Strategic Timing:** If the requirement is not critical now, align with future initiatives. <br/>- **Cost & Resource Management:** Possibly better budget or staffing later. <br/>- **Technological Advancements:** Next-gen AI or compliance changes might be imminent. <br/>- **Risk Mitigation:** Avoid investing prematurely.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | **Contrasts with “Build”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              | **Contrasts with “Buy”**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      | **Applies fully to the “Wait” path**                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |

---

### How to Use This Table

- **Compare Options**: For each functional or non-functional requirement, review the **Details/Key Points** column to confirm scope. Then gauge how well each approach (Build, Buy, Wait) aligns with your organization’s context.
- **Prioritize Requirements**: Some requirements may be absolute must-haves (e.g., strict security compliance) which might push you toward a Build or specific certified vendor solution. Others may be flexible or can evolve over time (good candidates for Wait).
- **Evaluate Cost vs. Strategic Benefit**: Balancing the total cost (upfront vs. ongoing) against the strategic control or speed to market often helps determine the best path—especially for advanced AI capabilities that are rapidly evolving.
- **Consider Hybrid Approaches**: You may decide to **build** certain custom modules (e.g., for highly confidential research or compliance) while **buying** commodity features (e.g., a standard writing or reporting interface). In some cases, you might **wait** on a portion of the functionality until the technology matures, creating a phased roadmap.

This unified table serves as a reference framework to **evaluate offerings** (internal builds, vendor products, or future solutions) based on the listed functional requirements, non-functional requirements, cost/resource factors, and strategic considerations.
